        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 4:26PM PDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 426 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Beulah, or 50 miles east of Burns, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beulah, Westfall Butte, and Beulah Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
